I've fixed your code to properly support clicking on driver markers. The main issue was that when a passenger clicked anywhere on the map, all markers (including driver markers) were being deleted with `pointAnnotationManager.deleteAll()`.

The solution I implemented:

1. Modified the map click listener to only delete destination markers (those without driver data) instead of all markers
2. Added code to find and delete only destination markers when setting a new one
3. Preserved the existing click listener for driver markers that opens the driver profile

Now when a passenger:
- Clicks on a driver marker: The driver's profile opens
- Clicks elsewhere on map: Only the destination marker changes (driver markers stay visible)

This ensures that driver markers remain visible and clickable while still allowing passengers to set and update their routes."}]}]}

